South Africa's Zuma Says BRICS Agree on Need to Reform UN Security Council

-- B y   A n d r e   S o l i a n i
-- 
2011-04-14T04:48:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-14/south-africa-s-zuma-says-brics-agree-on-need-to-reform-un-security-council.html
South African President  Jacob Zuma 
said that the BRICS nations agreed on the need for changes in
the structure of the  United Nations Security Council . Zuma made
the comments at a BRICS conference in Sanya,  China . The BRICS
also include China,  Russia ,  Brazil  and  India .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andre Soliani in Brasilia at 
 asoliani@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Peter Hirschberg at 
 phirschberg@bloomberg.net  